channel.title: Code Too Large
channel.description:
I have been recently working on my server, all was well until I was nearing the end of my new mini game. Suddenly I began to get this message while compiling
[code]client.java:13804: code too large public void parseIncomingPackets(){ ^ Note: stream.java uses or overrides a deprecated API. Note: Recompile with -Xlint:deprecation for details. 1 error[/code]
I can't seem to add any more things into my client.java without getting this message. I have tried deleting things and it goes away but I have no idea how to keep everything I have but add more! Anyone know what I should or could do to solve this? Thanks.

item.title: Code Too Large
item.dc:creator: @kihomura Kihomura
item.description:
@kihomura wrote:

Your packet is full. Say you have like an item on object code and it says code too large, that means your item on object packet is full. Clear your packet of the junk.

Read full topic
